groundspeak:cache.groundspeak:name: The I can't think of a good name Cache
groundspeak:cache.groundspeak:short_description: This should be a fairly easy park and grab located in Charles Town Square. If your looking for a long hike or some bushwacking you should pass on this cache :)
groundspeak:cache.groundspeak:long_description: I'm going to say that this is a micro. There is no room to trade any items at all and you Must bring your own Pen, a pencil will not do! PLEASE REMEMBER THE EXACT SPOT YOU FOUND THIS CACHE AND RETURN IT TO THAT SPOT PLEASE. I've stopped by to check a few times and always seem to find it in the wrong spot. Thanks!

groundspeak:log.groundspeak:text: Quick find while on a trip. Even after sunset, there was enough light to find it without a flashlight. TFTC!
